[2] Illinois (Ogle County)
Date: Wed 13 Nov 2019 5:44 PM CST
Source: WIFR [abridged, edited]
https://www.wifr.com/content/news/Ogle-County-investigates-pertussis-outbreak-at-Oregon-High-School-564864322.html


The Ogle County Health Department is investigating a pertussis outbreak at Oregon High School. The department says there are 8 positive cases of whooping cough at Oregon High School. Health officials are working with the school to prevent the further spread of the disease.

For more on the outbreak, contact the Ogle County Health Department at 815-562-6976.

