[5] Ohio (Springboro)
Date: Fri 15 Nov 2019
Source: WKRC Local 12 [abridged, edited]
https://local12.com/health/medical-edge-reports/infection-control-specialists-warning-of-whooping-cough-spreading-in-tri-state


There are new concerns as a highly contagious illness spreads in the Tri-State [Cincinnati metropolitan area, including Ohio, Kentucky, and Indiana].

Cases of pertussis, or whooping cough, are rapidly spreading. Springboro Schools sent a letter home to parents saying 26 cases of whooping cough have been confirmed at the schools so far. 17 of them have been treated and those students have been released to go back to school.

Springboro Schools spokesman Scott Marshall said those treated stayed home for at least 5 days, but they want to let the community know that they are recommending vaccinations for families because to very young children and also to older adults, this illness can be life-threatening.

[Byline: Liz Bonis]

--
